Best websites to refer for selenium locators :
https://blog.mozilla.org/fxtesteng/2013/09/26/writing-reliable-locators-for-selenium-and-webdriver-tests/
http://pragmatictestlabs.com/2020/01/28/mastering-xpath-for-selenium-test-automation-engineers/

Tip for selenium xpath and css :
Use the one generated by chrome browser => inspect => locate => copy Xpath/CSS
Then you get idea, then make your own out of it.
